data.name: cytoplasm
data.definition: All of the contents of a cell excluding the plasma membrane and nucleus, but including other subcellular structures.

data.name: cytoplasmic part
data.definition: Any constituent part of the cytoplasm, all of the contents of a cell excluding the plasma membrane and nucleus, but including other subcellular structures.

data.name: cellular_component
data.definition: A location, relative to cellular compartments and structures, occupied by a macromolecular machine when it carries out a molecular function. There are two ways in which the gene ontology describes locations of gene products: [1] relative to cellular structures [e.g., cytoplasmic side of plasma membrane] or compartments [e.g., mitochondrion], and [2] the stable macromolecular complexes of which they are parts [e.g., the ribosome].

data.name: cell part
data.definition: Any constituent part of a cell, the basic structural and functional unit of all organisms.

data.name: cytoplasm
data.definition: All of the contents of a cell excluding the plasma membrane and nucleus, but including other subcellular structures.

data.name: intracellular part
data.definition: Any constituent part of the living contents of a cell; the matter contained within [but not including] the plasma membrane, usually taken to exclude large vacuoles and masses of secretory or ingested material. In eukaryotes it includes the nucleus and cytoplasm.
